"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-16-2024-olympic-qualifier-cameroon-unveil-squad-for-super-falcons-clash\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Indomitable Lionesses of Cameroon head coach, Jean Baptiste Bisseck has listed 25 players for the team's 2024 Olympic Games qualifying fixture against Nigeria.  Bisseck also named four players on the reserve list.  All the invited players ply their trade in the Cameroonian league.  The Indomitable Lionesses will look to qualify for the Olympics after missing out on a place at the 2024 Africa Women's Cup of Nations.  Cameroon will host the first leg at the Stade de la Reunification in Douala, Cameroon on Friday, February 23.  The second leg match will take place at the MKO Abiola National Stadium, Abuja on Monday, February 26th.  Congratulations Haller, Super Eagles fell short at AFCON final - Ademola Lookman  Euro 2024: 'They can do it' - Mourinho predicts country to win trophy  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"